@Jack  Thank you! I use a combination of Crosserville and Ingrid for construction. 

I spend a ton of time on my puzzles trying to make the fill as clean and fresh as possible, so that really means a lot to me! My primary wordlists are Spread the Wordlist and the Crosserville default list (OneLook is also a helpful tool for finding entries). I have recently started putting more effort into rescoring any entries I think should be higher/lower as well as adding entries to my own personal wordlist. My best advice is to be intentional with fill (upscoring entries you enjoy while downscoring/rejecting fill you don't) and flexible with the grid (adding/removing black squares to look).

Best of luck on your construction journey!

